text.tspan: first you need to sharpen you're engineering foundation
Learn about the famous design pattern so you can
solve most of the problems you face in a better engineering way
try to learn about TDD by creating a mini project that you can implement TDD roles.
writing in TDD will make you learn how to write better clean testable code.
So it this step try to write more and more code.
Try to implement mini packages/project in TDD
4 Read more and more open-source projects
Reading others code is the best way you can learn how to write clean code.
If you're an open-source developer, you can check your favorite framework's
codebase. You can even start exploring the code of the packages you use frequently.
At this step, github should be the most opened website on your browser history ;)
5 Try to write unit tests/refactor one of your old codebases.
Writing unit tests for your old un-covered codebase.
At this step you can pick one of your old projects and try
to write unit tests for it. For sure you'll find many functions/classes
that are not testable at all, here start detecting these areas and start refactoring it.
6 Start contributing to some open-source projects
This can be done in many ways:
a. you can start by exploring your beloved packages on github.
you'll find some issues created by the community.
Try to contribute and solve these issues
b. You can check some improvement in the code and start applying
c. You can write more unit tests and raise the code coverage
7 At this step, you'll need to join a team that does really...
At this step you'll really need to join a team that has at least one good architect
that can help you/review your code. Always remember "architecture is being learnt by doing!"
The most hard part at this step is gaining the trust from the people around to let you
lead the design and the implementation of the projects.
